import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
plt.rc("font", size=14)
plt.figure(figsize=(15,8))

# I would like to see the histogram distribution for King County house price
# First let me derive histogram 10 histogram bins

## range(house.price.min(), house.price.max(), (house.price.max()-house.price.min())/10)
myBins = np.arange(house.price.min(), house.price.max(), (house.price.max()-house.price.min())/20)

ax = house.price.hist(bins = myBins, color='teal', alpha=0.8)
ax.set(xlabel='Price', ylabel='Count')
plt.show()

# King County house price is (right) skewed, let's check if mean and median are different
print("median price of house in King County", house.price.median())
print("average price of house in King County", house.price.mean())
